We were honoured to participate in the 44th Annual State Conference of the Indian Radiological & Imaging Association (IRIA), Calicut City Chapter, held at  Hotel KPM Tripenta, Calicut (Kozhikode) on November 15-16, 2025!

The conference served as a vibrant platform bringing together radiologists, imaging specialists, researchers, educators, and healthcare entrepreneurs from across India. It was an enriching experience to connect with brilliant minds who continue to shape the future of diagnostic imaging and radiology.

At Phantom Healthcare, we take immense pride in being part of such prestigious gatherings that celebrate innovation and collaboration in medical imaging. Our continued efforts are dedicated to:

ð¹ Supplying genuine spare parts and upgrades to minimize downtime and optimise clinical efficiency
ð¹ Supporting hospitals, diagnostic centres, and clinics with end-to-end installation, training, and service solutions

Every event like IRIA reaffirms our mission â to make advanced imaging technology affordable, accessible, and sustainable, empowering healthcare providers to deliver precise and timely diagnoses.

A heartfelt thanks to the IRIA Calicut City Chapter for hosting such a well-organised and inspiring event. We look forward to contributing further to Indiaâs evolving radiology landscape.

We are proud to have participated in MID-TERM CME 2025, organized by the Musculoskeletal Society of India in collaboration with the Indian Radiological & Imaging Association- IRIA M.P. Chapter. This prestigious event took place on Sunday, 23rd March 2025, at Chirayu Medical College & Hospital, Bhopal (Chirayu University).

ð¬ What is MID-TERM CME?
Continuing Medical Education (CME) programs are designed to help healthcare professionals stay updated with the latest advancements in their field. A Mid-Term CME serves as an interim educational event between major annual conferences, providing radiologists and medical practitioners with focused insights into emerging trends and technologies.

With the theme "Imaging and Interventions in Musculoskeletal Infections & Inflammation," the conference brought together leading radiologists, musculoskeletal imaging specialists, and healthcare professionals to discuss cutting-edge techniques in diagnostics and interventions for musculoskeletal disorders.

At Phantom Healthcare, we are dedicated to empowering the radiology community with refurbished MRI, CT, PET-CT, and Cath Lab systems, ensuring affordable, high-quality diagnostic imaging solutions for healthcare providers across India.

A heartfelt thank you to the Musculoskeletal Society of India and the Indian Radiological & Imaging Association (IRIA) M.P. Chapter for organizing such an insightful and engaging conference. We look forward to continuing our journey of advancing radiology and medical imaging across the country!

We are honored to have been part of NCSICON 2025, the 15th Biennial Conference of the Nuclear Cardiological Society of India, held on March 8th-9th, 2025, at Sarvodaya Hospital, Sector 8, Faridabad.

This prestigious event brought together some of the most renowned experts, researchers, and professionals in nuclear cardiology to discuss the latest advancements, innovations, and trends shaping the future of cardiovascular imaging and diagnostics. As a company committed to revolutionizing medical imaging through high-quality refurbished MRI, CT, PET-CT, and Cath lab systems, we are always eager to engage with the healthcare community and contribute to meaningful discussions on technology-driven patient care.

A big thank you to the organizers for curating an insightful and knowledge-rich platform. We look forward to more opportunities to support and collaborate in the advancement of nuclear cardiology.

National Science Day is celebrated in India every year on 28 February to mark the discovery of the Raman Effect by Indian physicist Sir C.V. Raman on February 28, 1928. The Raman effect refers to the scattering of light by molecules, and this discovery earned Raman the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1930.

The celebration of National Science Day is an important event for India as it encourages the country's youth to take an interest in science and technology and promote scientific research and development in the country.

media.title: IRIA & AOCR 2025, Chennai - Phantom Healthcare
media.description:
A Successful Showcase at IRIA & AOCR 2025, Chennai - Phantom Healthcare

ð Reflecting on an Incredible Journey at IRIA & AOCR 2025! ð
The prestigious IRIA & AOCR 2025 conference in Chennai was a phenomenal experience for Phantom Healthcare! Over the course of this landmark event, we connected with an incredible audience comprising doctors, scientists, researchers, entrepreneurs, and healthcare innovators from across the globe.

ð¡ Unveiling Innovation:
Our booth was a hub of energy and curiosity, where visitors got a closer look at the future of radiology. The cutaway (open-cut) models of MRI and PET-CT machines were undoubtedly a showstopper. These intricate displays provided a behind-the-scenes view of the advanced engineering that powers modern diagnostic systems. Visitors were fascinated by the precision and expertise that go into these imaging technologies, sparking engaging discussions about their role in transforming healthcare.

ð Global Networking & Knowledge Sharing:
The conference provided an exceptional platform to share insights, explore collaborations, and discuss the ever-evolving field of radiology. We showcased how Phantom Healthcare is bridging gaps in diagnostics with our refurbished imaging solutions, state-of-the-art technology, and sustainable practices. The conversations reinforced our commitment to empowering healthcare providers with affordable, high-quality diagnostic solutions.

ð¤ Building Connections & Driving Impact:
We were privileged to meet like-minded professionals and explore partnerships aimed at improving access to diagnostics worldwide. From showcasing our AMC/CMC services, turnkey solutions, and largest inventory of spare parts to highlighting our rigorous testing standards, Phantom Healthcare proudly demonstrated why weâre a leader in the refurbished imaging industry.

ð Highlights of the Event:
Showcasing our expertise in MRI, CT, PET-CT, Cath Lab, Bone Densitometer, and Gamma Camera systems
Interacting with global leaders and sharing our mission to redefine radiology
Building awareness about our largest inventory of spare parts and cutting-edge refurbishment processes

media.description:
We are thrilled to invite you to the 23rd Asian Oceanian Congress of Radiology (AOCR 2025) and the 77th Annual Conference of the Indian Radiological & Imaging Association (IRIA 2025), scheduled to take place from January 23 to 26, 2025, at the Chennai Trade Centre, Nandambakkam, Chennai, Tamil Nadu, India.

Theme: "Clinical Radiology Decoded â See like a Surgeon: Think Like a Physician"

Organizers: Hosted by the Tamil Nadu & Pondicherry Chapter of the Indian Radiological & Imaging Association (IRIA) and the Asian Oceanian Society of Radiology (AOSR).

Phantom Healthcare is proud to be one of the leading exhibitors at this prestigious event. Having participated in the IRIA Annual Conference for many years, we remain committed to supporting the growth of the radiology community. Join us at our stall to explore the latest in refurbished medical imaging equipment, including MRI, CT, PET-CT, Bone Densitometer DEXA, Gamma Camera SPECT, CATH lab machines, and more.

Key Highlights:

Scientific Sessions: Engage with leading experts through interactive lectures and hands-on workshops.
Networking Opportunities: Connect with professionals and industry leaders from around the world.
Exhibition: Discover cutting-edge technologies in medical imaging and radiology.
Registration Details:

We look forward to seeing you in Chennai for an enriching and memorable experience!

Organizers: Hosted by the Tamil Nadu & Pondicherry Chapter of the Indian Radiological & Imaging Association (IRIA) and the Asian Oceanian Society of Radiology (AOSR).

About IRIA & AOSR:
IRIA (Indian Radiological & Imaging Association), founded in 1951, is India's leading professional body dedicated to the growth and development of radiology and medical imaging. The association brings together radiologists, radiographers, and imaging professionals to promote research, education, and best practices in the field of radiology. With a strong network of members, IRIA organizes various scientific conferences, workshops, and training programs, making it a significant player in shaping the future of radiology in India.

AOSR (Asian Oceanian Society of Radiology), established in 1981, is an international organization that serves as a collaborative platform for radiology professionals across the Asia-Pacific region. AOSR aims to promote radiology practices, research, and education, and to provide opportunities for networking and knowledge exchange among professionals. Its flagship event, the Asian Oceanian Congress of Radiology (AOCR), gathers experts from around the world to discuss the latest innovations and developments in radiology.

World Brain Tumor Day 2024

World Brain Tumor Day is celebrated every year on the 8th of June to make people aware of growing brain tumours globally and educate them on preventive measures.

Symptoms of a brain tumour depend on the location and size of the tumour. Some tumours directly damage the brain tissues and some tumours pressure the surrounding parts. It's most common to have headaches often. Along with this if you are feeling some other symptoms for a long time then you should consult a doctor.

âHeadache or pressure which is high in the morning.
âBeing nauseous or vomiting often.
âEye problems, such as blurred appearance or double vision.
âNot functioning properly of one arm or one leg.
âDifficulty in physical-mental balance.
âKeep feeling so tired.
âDetect tumours by MRI and CT scan

#WorldBrainTumorDay #Braintumor #Brainhealth #Awareness #Treatment #MRI #CT #Consultdoctor #Scan #Hypertension #Healthcare

Phantom Healthcare is one of the leading exhibitors at this conference. Please visit us at our Stall No. P-5 at the Venue: Rajasthan International Center, Bhamashah State Data Centre Block-C, Bhamashah State Data Centre, Jhalana Doongri, Jaipur, Rajasthan -at Rajasthan International Centre, jaipur

30th State Annual Conference of the Indian Radiological & Imaging Association [IRIA] to be hosted by the Rajasthan State Chapter of IRIA.

When do doctors suggest cardiac MRI Scans?

Cardiac MRI (Magnetic Resonance Imaging) scans are a valuable diagnostic tool that doctors may recommend for various reasons when assessing heart health and related conditions. Here are some common situations when doctors suggest cardiac MRI scans

â Assessment of Heart Function
â Assessment of Valve Function
â Identification of Congenital Heart Defects
â Assessment of Cardiac Tumors
â Assessment of Blood Vessels
â Preoperative Planning
â Monitoring Disease Progression
â Others

It's important to note that the decision to recommend a cardiac MRI scan will depend on the patient's specific medical history, symptoms, and the information needed for diagnosis and treatment planning. Cardiac MRI is a non-invasive and safe imaging modality.

media.title: Timeline photos
media.description:
Empowering healthcare affordably is a vital goal, and one effective approach is through the adoption of refurbished MRI technology. By choosing to upgrade with refurbished MRI machines, healthcare facilities can benefit from modern imaging capabilities at a significantly lower cost compared to purchasing new equipment. This prudent investment enables healthcare providers to enhance diagnostic accuracy, leading to better patient care and treatment outcomes.

Additionally, the cost savings obtained through refurbished technology can be redirected to other critical areas, ensuring improved accessibility and quality of healthcare services for a broader range of patients. In this way, leveraging refurbished MRI technology proves to be a smart and compassionate way to make healthcare more affordable and accessible for all.

World Brain Tumor Day is celebrated every year on the 8th of June to make people aware of growing brain tumours globally and educate them on preventive measures.

Symptoms of a brain tumour depend on the location and size of the tumour. Some tumours directly damage the brain tissues and some tumours pressure the surrounding parts. It's most common to have headaches often. Along with this if you are feeling some other symptoms for a long time then you should consult a doctor.

On this women's day, we would like to give a memento of gratitude to our Managing Director and CEO of Phantom Healthcare Ms. Rochi Nargotra, she has been an inspiration to the entire organization. She is a real example of a successful women leader. 

Our country and world need more examples like her who can take leadership in various domains and fields of professions. Female participation is very crucial for any nation or society to flourish and grow. 

She is inspiring females to be part of the biomedical technology industry.
Showing a glimpse of "THROWBACK FROM THE PAST"-- When Our CEO, Ms. Rochi Nargotra received "The Women Entrepreneur of the Year Award" from Mr. Vijay Goel then Hon'ble Minister of State for Statistics and Programme Implementation, This event was the Annual Business Submit of Business Sphere Magazine in September 2018.

data.post:
On this women's day, we would like to give a memento of gratitude to our Managing Director and CEO of Phantom Healthcare Ms. Rochi Nargotra, she has been an inspiration to the entire organization. She is a real example of a successful women leader. 

Our country and world need more examples like her who can take leadership in various domains and fields of professions. Female participation is very crucial for any nation or society to flourish and grow. 

She is inspiring females to be part of the biomedical technology industry.
Showing a glimpse of "THROWBACK FROM THE PAST"-- When Our CEO, Ms. Rochi Nargotra received "The Women Entrepreneur of the Year Award" from Mr. Vijay Goel then Hon'ble Minister of State for Statistics and Programme Implementation, This event was the Annual Business Submit of Business Sphere Magazine in September 2018.

data.post:
What is the role of Cardiac Imaging?
Cardiac imaging refers to the use of various imaging techniques to visualize the structure and function of the heart. This can help in the diagnosis, treatment, and monitoring of various cardiovascular diseases.

Types of Cardiac Imaging

1. Echocardiography
2. Coronary Catheterization
3. Cardiovascular Radiology
4. Cardiothoracic Radiology
5. Angiography

Echocardiography
Transthoracic echocardiography uses ultrasonic waves for continuous heart chambers and blood movement visualization. It allows non-invasive visualization of the heart and the blood flow through the heart, using a technique known as Doppler.

Coronary Catheterization
Coronary Catheterization is a minimally invasive procedure to access the coronary circulation and blood-filled chambers of the heart using a catheter. It is performed for both diagnostic and interventional (treatment) purposes.

Cardiovasular Radiology
Cardiovascular Radiology is the subspecialty of radiology devoted to the diagnostic imaging and diagnosis of disease of the heart and diagnosis of diseases of the heart and blood vessels (including the arteries and veins, and the lymphatics).

Cardiothoracic Radiology
Cardiothoracic Radiology consists of the application and interpretation of imaging examinations and interventional procedures related to the lungs, pleura, mediastinum, chest wall, heart, pericardium, and thoracic vascular system in the adult.

Angiography
Angiography is used to check the health of your blood vessels and how blood flows through them. It can help to diagnose or investigate several problems affecting blood vessels. Blood Vessels do not show clearly on a normal X-ray, so a special dye needs to be injected into your blood first.

Techniques Used
MRI Scan
CT Scan
PET Scan
X-rays
Ultrasound

National Science Day is celebrated in India every year on 28 February to mark the discovery of the Raman Effect by Indian physicist Sir C.V. Raman on February 28, 1928. The Raman effect refers to the scattering of light by molecules, and this discovery earned Raman the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1930.

The celebration of National Science Day is an important event for India as it encourages the youth of the country to take interest in science and technology and to promote scientific research and development in the country.

media.description:
PHANTOM HEALTHCARE IND Pvt Limited SUCCESSFULLY ATTENDED IRIA 2023, Amritsar.IRIA 2023  was "The Confluence Of Entire Indian Culture at the Land of Peace & Patriotism, at Amritsar Punjab".

Phantom Healthcare emerged as "The Showstopper Of The Event", Our Stall took the entire limelight at the conference. We were the center of attraction among all the exhibitors. 

We were one of the leading exhibitors at this conference.
It was another impactful mark in the community of medical technologists.
We were successful in strengthening belief and faith In the hearts Of radiological professionals.
We were overwhelmed by receiving words of praise from our clients which is far more valuable than any monetary benefits.

We Extend Our Gratitude To All The Doctors, Researchers, and Healthcare Professionals Who Gave Us The Opportunity To Interact And Intended To Join Us In The Future.  

IRIA Annual Conference is the biggest Medical Event in the field of radiology and medical imaging where leading medical professionals, doctors, researchers, and scientists participate and collaborate.

The 75th Annual conference of the Indian Radiological & Imaging Association [IRIA] was hosted by the Punjab State Chapter of IRIA along with State Chapters of Haryana, Himachal Pradesh, Jammu and Kashmir, Ladakh & Chandigarh as Co-Host.

This deal marked the expansion of international partners for Glassbeam beyond current (American) U.S. installations.

media.description:
National Girl Child Day 2023: It is celebrated on 24 January in India to spread awareness about the rights of girls and to highlight the inequalities that they face in their lives.

Female foeticide is another major issue that further affects the demographic problems in India.
The PC-PNDT Act was enacted on 20 September 1994 with the intent to prohibit prenatal diagnostic techniques for the determination of the sex of the fetus leading to female feticide. 

This also to promote awareness about the rights of the girl child and the importance of female education, health, and nutrition. The day is in line with various campaigns and programs of the Indian government including Beti Bachao Beti Padhao and Save the Girl Child.

January is Cervical Cancer Awareness Month. It is a perfect opportunity for WHO and partners to raise awareness about cervical cancer and HPV vaccination that can help prevent certain types of cancers.

Cervical Cancer Awareness Month, is a great time to talk about how human papillomavirus (HPV) vaccines can help prevent cancer. Cervical cancer was once the leading cause of cancer death for women in the world. Now, thanks to cervical cancer screening and HPV vaccination, it is the most preventable of all female cancers.

media.title: What Is The Missile Effect in an MRI?  The "Missile Effect" Refers to the capability of an MRI Magnetic field to attract a ferromagnetic object into the scanner with considerable force.
media.description:
What Is The Missile Effect in an MRI?

The "Missile Effect" Refers to the capability of an MRI Magnetic field to attract a ferromagnetic object into the scanner with considerable force.

Examples of ferromagnetic objects:-- Ferromagnetic metal alloys usually contain iron, nickel, or cobalt. These elements are found in most metal objects.

The "Missile Effect" can pose a significant risk to a patient in the scanner and to anyone who is in the path of the attracted object.

Metal objects can become dangerous projectiles if they are taken into the scan room!

Results of The Missile Effect:
-Delayed patient Care.
-It takes 4 days to remove the object and to re-power the scanner.
-Possible injury to patients or staff.
-Possible Damage to The MRI Scanner.

Approximate cost Due to Each "Missile Effect" Incident: $250,000.

media.description:
World Braille Day 2023.
LOUIS BRAILLE (4 JAN, 1809 - 6 JAN, 1852)

Born in France. He was 3 when he lost his eyes while playing with some tools in his father's workshop.

Braille's system was adopted in 1854, two years after his death.
At the age of 15, he developed the 6-dot fingertip reading system known as the Braille system and it was inspired by a military system of 'Night writing' which assisted soldiers in communicating in the dark without sound and light.

The Encyclopedia Britannica lists him among the "100 Most Influential Inventors of All Time". His birthday is celebrated every year as World Braille Day to recognize his efforts.

media.description:
Why do we need Pelvic MRI? 

-- For women, a pelvic MRI is used to evaluate the ovaries and uterus as a follow-up to an ultrasound exam that showed an abnormality. It Is also used to assess endometrial cancer. For men, pelvic MRI is sometimes used to evaluate prostate cancer.

media.description:
November 8 is observed annually as World Radiology Day or International Day of Radiology (IDoR) to commemorate the discovery of X-radiation, or X-rays, on November 8, 1895, by German scientist Wilhelm Conrad Rontgen, who, in 1901, became the inaugural winner of the Nobel Prize in Physics for this achievement. 
The field of radiology revolutionized modern medicine giving us so many modalities to both diagnose as well as treat various diseases
We thank all radiologists and radiographers around the world for the critical role they play in patient care.

media.description:
Principles of the MRI

1. Spinning Atoms (hydrogen) face outside the magnetic field
2. Energy Absorption by RF Coils.
3. Resonance of Hydrogen atoms Measured by RF antenna which the received signal is sinusoidal in shape
4. Imaging by the computer which receives mathematical data, which is converted through the use of a Fourier transform into an image

media.description:
TYPES OF MRI MAGNETS

1. Superconducting magnet
-Very high voltages are used 
-Wire winded on coil & electrically applied the ends
-More voltage greater the field 

2. Permanent magnet 
-Heavyweight 
-Full strength 
-Low cost 
-Internal core is made of it that generates magnet field all the time 
-Rotor Coils Commutator

3. Resistive magnet
- Internal x-axis is controlled by a resistive magnet
- A portion of imaging is controlled
- Direction around an iron core

If your MRI magnet is not working and you need to change it, you can contact Phantom Healthcare. We are capable of altering your MRI magnet at an affordable price.

media.description:
Why MRI Is Better Than X-Rays?

X-Rays

1. Creates 2D images
2. Used primarily to see bones and detect pneumonia
3. Most common & widely available for small or minor issues
4. Use radiation to produce Images
5. Economical and cost-efficient

MRI

1. Creates 3D images and is mainly used in complex and major diseases
2. Used to scan spines, brain, and muscles, using radio waves
3. Uses a powerful magnet and generates detailed images
4. Create cross-section images of organs & tissues
5. Expensive and used only when advised by doctors

What's The Difference Between MRI & CT Scan 

------MRI scan ------

1. Uses strong magnetic and radio waves 
2. .Pr Produces very detailed 3D images of soft tissue 
3. Good for seeing organs & bony details 
4. Duration time of MRI Scanner is a bit longer 

-------------- CT scan--------------- 

1. Uses low doses of radiation 
2. Produces detailed images of bones & blood vessels 
3. Good for seeing soft tissue Duration time of CT Scanner is quick

National Doctor's Day in India.
Doctors bring health and hope.
On #DoctorsDay, we extend our greetings to all the hardworking doctors, who have devoted themselves towards the welfare of humanity. The world will never forget the efforts & sacrifices of our doctors during the toughest times of the COVID pandemic.
Extending our heartfelt gratitude to the entire medical fraternity who are tirelessly serving in these terrible times. Their contribution in combating #COVID19 is unparalleled.
Our humble tribute to former CM of West Bengal, Dr. Bidhan Chandra Roy, on his birth anniversary which is celebrated as National Doctor's Day in India.
#Doctors #HappyDoctorsDay
#DoctorsDay
#DoctorsOnROad #NationalDoctorsDay #ThankYouDoctors #DoctorsDay2022

--

The technology allows for vivid, anatomically correct images of the brain.
It could potentially be used to detect brain conditions ranging from aneurysms to hydrocephalus.

media.description:
WHAT IS MRI ALIASING? 
----
Aliasing in MRI, also known as wrap-around, is a frequently encountered MRI artifact that occurs when field view (FOV) is smaller than the body part being imaged. The part of the body that lies beyond the edge of the FOV is projected onto the other side of the image.

November 8 is observed annually as World Radiology Day or International Day of Radiology (IDoR) to commemorate the discovery of X-radiation, or X-rays, on November 8, 1895, by German scientist Wilhelm Conrad Rontgen, who, in 1901, became the inaugural winner of the Nobel Prize in Physics for this achievement. 
For IDoR 2021, we have chosen the motto âInterventional Radiology â Active care for the patientâ.

The objective behind observing such a day is to raise public awareness of radiographic imaging and therapy, which plays a significant role in the diagnosis and treatment of patients. WHAT IS A SURFACE COIL IN MRI? 

- Surface coils are types of receive-only radiofrequency coil used in MRI to receive radiofrequency signal (transmitted the body coil). Surface coils are small and are shaped so that they can be placed near the part of anatomy being imaged.

ARE MRI IMAGES FLIPPED?

- It is common that coronal images on Shoulder MRI Exams come up flipped almost always left side. This pitfall is related to the high obliquity (45 or higher) of the shoulder (Figure 1), leading to a swap in phase and direction.

CAN MRI DETECT LIVER FIBROSIS? 
-- MRI based MR Elastography (MRE) (Magnetic Resonance Elastography) has been shown to be a promising technique for the detection of liver fibrosis. TE (Transient elastography) and MRE are the most commonly used elastography techniques for the assessment of liver fibrosis.

WHAT IS T2 FLAIR ON MRI? 

FLAIR MRI is heavily T2-weighted technique that dampens the ventricular (free-water) CSF signal. Thus, the highest signals sequence are from certain brain parenchymal abnormalities, such as MS lesions, while the CSF appears black.

WHY WOULD A CHILD NEED AN MRI? 

MRI is used to help diagnose a wide range of conditions in children due to injury, illness, or congenital abnormalities. When imaging of a child's brain spinal cord is needed, MRI is useful because of its ability to see through the skull and the bones of the skull and spine without radiation.

media.description:
Independence day celebrations at our Phantom Healthcare Headquarters in Faridabad. Guest of Honour were our respected CEO & MD Mrs Rochi Nargotra and MD Mr Brijesh Suneja. An MRI (magnetic resonance imaging) creates detailed images of organs and tissues. 

An MRA (magnetic resonance angiography) focuses more on the blood vessels than the tissue surrounding it.

Does MRI Scans have any side effects ?

MRI does not use radiation (X-rays) and is a noninvasive because radiation is not used, there is no risk of exposure to radiation during an MRI procedure. However, due to the use of the strong magnet, MRI cannot be performed on patients with implants, any pacemakers or metals used in body.
